### Description

It would be nicer if we could trigger a reload of the latest set of parameters before undefined what set.

### Proposed solution

Example: 

request = signal({ param1: 'test1', param2: 'test2' });
onOff = signal(true);

resource = rxResource({
    stream: () => this.onOff() ? this.request() : undefined
    loader: ({ params }) => this.api.loader(params)
}); // first request triggered

this.onOff.set(false); // the resource doesn't react anymore to request signal change
this.request.update(value => ({ ...value, params2: 'other value' });
// Now it would be useful to be able to trigger manually the resource with the last valid (not undefined) request signal value
this.resource.reload() // request: { param1: 'test1', param2: 'other value' }

### Alternatives considered

doing everything in the loader function which is untracked.

### Description

When `mat-form-field` contains `mat-error` with a simple `@if`, then it is rendered properly. However, if we nest `@if`, error will be squished inside the form, instead of being present in `mat-mdc-form-field-subscript-wrapper`.

```
<mat-form-field appearance="outline">
  <input formControlName="bbb" matInput/>
      @if ( true ) {
        <mat-error>Nice error</mat-error>
      }
</mat-form-field>
```

### Reproduction

https://stackblitz.com/edit/stackblitz-starters-nhxdncvv?file=src%2Fmain.ts

### Expected Behavior

Renders properly:
<img width="277" height="108" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/41303499-b3a8-4d15-9f5e-425769070eeb" />

```
@if( true ) {
  <mat-error>Nice error</mat-error>
}
```

### Actual Behavior

Doesn't render properly:
<img width="277" height="114" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/16f86d10-dee9-471d-acdf-3467416a6e3f" />
```
@if( true ) {
  @if ( true ) {
    <mat-error>Terrible error</mat-error>
  }
}
```

### Environment

- Angular: 21
- CDK/Material: 21

